title.narrative: Capacity of child protection actors to prevent and respond to cases of violence against children strengthened at national and decentralised level and access of children and families to child protection services, increased.

description.narrative: Thanks to UNICEF's assistance, 30,000 children received their birth certificates and nine new civil registration services started operating at health facilities, increasing to 24, the total of functioning units. 562 children at risks were referred and assisted by State and NGOs Child Protection services, especially by the decentralized social service workforce at the justice and health sectors. At community level, under the UNICEF/UNFPA programmes, UNICEF contributed to mobilizing 43,077 people towards the abandonment of FGM, with 20 new communities declaring abandonment of FGM and child marriage, raising to a total of 303 the number communities committed to ending harmful practices. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
